data.name: btn_read_vCard.ToolTip
data.value:
Import Contacts from the standardised vCard file format. This has been tested with GoogleMail, Apple Adressbook and jFritz vCard export files.
Keep SHIFT pressed for source files that are not encoded in UNICODE Format!

data.name: combo_prefix.ToolTip
data.value:
Please select the country you are in, so that the international dialling prefixes can be correctly removed when exporting.
If you select Custom, you will be asked for the prefix while exporting to a file.

data.name: btn_read_FritzAdress.ToolTip
data.value:
Imports contacts from AVM's Fritz!Adr Adressbook.
You need to export your Fritz!Adr contacts first, please select "Text separated by Tabstops" when exporting! (and then import the generated TXT file here)

data.name: btn_save_vCard.ToolTip
data.value:
Export contacts for use in programs and services that can import vCard files. Keep SHIFT pressed to export only contacts that have a home/work/mobile number.
The exported file should be VCARD 3.0 compliant and is UTF8-encoded.

data.name: btn_save_SnomCSV8.ToolTip
data.value:
Complex CSV Export for Snom Phones with v8.x Firmware: Exports: Combined Name / First Name / Last Name / Number / eMail, with full support for subcontacts and VIP flag!
File Format is UTF8 without BOM.

data.name: btn_save_panasonicCSV.ToolTip
data.value:
Export for Panasonic - KX-TCD810/815/816 - KX-TCD820/825/826 - KX-TG1890/1895 using USB GEAR Software from http://panasonic.net/pcc/support/tel/tcd800series.htm
Be aware that special characters like the asterisk may not be handled correctly by the panasonic software and have to be entered into the phone directly.

data.name: btn_save_vCard_Gigaset.ToolTip
data.value:
Export contacts for use in Gigaset Phones (tested with DX600A) using a simplified vCard Format. By default exports only contacs that have a home/work/mobile number. E-Mail will also be stored.
The exported file may be VCARD 2.1 compliant and is UTF8-without-BOM-encoded.

data.name: combo_typeprefer.ToolTip
data.value:
vCard Import: Affects selection of Address and eMail Fritz!Adr Import: Affects whether Phone/Fax Nr. are imported into Home or Work fields Outlook Import: Affects whether Other Phone numbers are preferrably put in Home or Work Google Import: Affects whether Main Phone numbers are preferrably put in Home or Work
vCard Export: Affects export of Address as either Work or Home Adress Google Export: Affects export of Address as either Work or Home Adress
Other Import/Export Methods than those above: This option has no effect.

data.name: combo_namestyle.ToolTip
data.value:
Effects during Import: Since many export formats (Fritz!Box XML, Fritz!Adr, Snom v7, Grandstream GXP and others) only provide a single field for name, a combined name has to be generated from Firstname Lastname and Company. Here you can select in what way this combined field will be generated during import.
Effects during Export: In specific export formats that - support multiple numbers per contact - have separate firstname and lastname fields - do NOT have a company field usage of an option without company here makes the export ignore the company in these specific cases and thereby allows the export to put firstname and lastname in the corresponding separate fields. This behavior currently affects - Gigaset vCard export - Grandstream GXV export For contact entries that do not have a company set, separate firstname and lastname fields are automatically used irrespective of this option.

data.name: combo_outlookimport.ToolTip
data.value: When importing contacts from Outlook, you can choose here whether the "Combined Name" field will be generated according to the Combined Name Style you have selected (default), or whether the Combined Name field will be filled with the contents of Outlooks FileAs field.
